Solution by Sudhamshu B N
Use App Engine to build microservices (This provides the necessary scale and easy replication)
Use Cloud Deployment Manager to deploy applications and implement a CI/CD pipeline
Use Global HTTP(S) Proxy and allow it to divert traffic in the scenario of disaster recovery
Encryption is provided at rest by default, provide option of managing CSEK(Customer Supplied Encryption Key)
Use Firewall to filter and allow only HTTPS traffic and setup certificates
Move MySQL to Cloud SQL
Use Cloud dataproc for batch processing and Hadoop/Spark workload
Use Cloud Pub/Sub for messaging
Use Cloud Storage as storage bucket, will probably need to build a cloud interconnect connection if we plan to keep the data center or move it via offline disk mailing option
You could build Jenkins in the Cloud via a provisioned VM with Jenkins
